      "title": "SLFP decides to amend party constitution to penalize violators",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Central Committee of the Sri Lanka Freedom Party has agreed on amending its party constitution in a way that empowers the central committee and the party leadership in expelling party members who act in a manner detrimental to the policies and rules of the party.",
        "The Party Secretary Dayasiri Jayasekara stated that this decision was reached during a discussion held at the party headquarters on Thursday (1) evening."
      ],
